******
[2] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Fri 9 May 2008
Source: JB Online [in Portuguese, trans & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://jbonline.terra.com.br/extra/2008/05/09/e090517806.html>


The number of dengue cases in the city of Rio de Janeiro has passed 76 000.
As the last weekly update by the municipal secretary of health (SMS)
disclosed this on Friday [9 May 2008], those infected since 1 Jan 2008
total 76 385. An additional 1769 cases were confirmed by the Secretariat.
In the state of Rio, there have been 134 643 cases. According to SMS, no
new deaths have been recorded in the last 48 hours.

On Wednesday [7 May 2008], the State Secretariat of Health (SES) released
another weekly update showing the number of dengue cases in the state of
Rio de Janeiro. The update indicated 3 new deaths were confirmed, bringing
the number of fatal victims to 106 in 2008. The city of Rio leads the list
with 64 deaths. There were no recorded new deaths in the last 2 days.

--
